AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 450* House Bill No. 641
by deleting SECTION 2 and substituting instead:
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 9-4-213, is amended by adding the
following new subsections:
(e)
(1) Each December, when the state funding board presents its state
revenue estimates in accordance with ยง 9-4-5202(e)(3), the board shall also
certify the growth rate of the state general fund revenue based on actual revenue
collections from the prior fiscal year.
(2) If the growth rate that is certified for the prior fiscal year under
subdivision (e)(1) equals or exceeds one percent (1%), then the base amount of
the contracts of the child advocacy center in each judicial district must be
increased on the subsequent July 1 by three percent (3%) for the purpose of
providing services to child victims.
(f) Subject to appropriation, the department of children's services shall increase
the base amount for each child advocacy center contract as follows:
(1) A contract labeled as "child advocacy center" must be increased to a
base of one hundred twenty-seven thousand eight hundred fifty-five dollars and
ninety-eight cents ($127,855.98); and
(2) A contract labeled as "forensic child interviewer" must be increased to
a base of eighty-five thousand dollars ($85,000) per contracted interviewer.
